jobs_results.title: MOBILE DEVELOPER (H/F)
jobs_results.description:
Mobile Developer

Job Overview

New project do develop top cutting Edge Mobile app on both common platform IoS and Android and using adaptative UI for Android Auto and Apple CarPlay.

Responsibilities for Mobile Developer
• Identify and plan for new features
• Develop application programming interfaces (APIs) to support mobile functionality (based on AWS frameworks)
• Suggest and implement new mobile products, applications and protocols
• Remain up to date with the terminology, concepts and best practices for coding mobile apps
• Work closely with colleagues to constantly innovate app functionality and design
• Use and adapt existing web applications for apps
• Write unit and UI tests to identify malfunctions
• Communicate with users to understand their needs and experiences

Qualifications for Mobile Developer
• 3+ years of demonstrable experience
• Demonstrable portfolio of released applications on the App store or the Android market
• Extensive knowledge of at least one programming language like Swift and Amplify or Java
• Familiarity with OOP design principles
• Experience with third-party libraries and APIs (mostly AWS), Maps and géolocalisation services.
• Superior analytical skills with a good problem-solving attitude
• Ability to perform in a team environment
• Strong oral and written communication skills (English or French)
• Ability to interpret and follow technical plans

2 / AWS DevOps Architect

Job Overview

We are looking for a DevOps architect to manage the software development process and create an automated delivery pipeline that assists in building software more efficiently. The responsibilities of a DevOps architect include assessing, supporting, and implementing high-quality information technology architecture.

To be successful as a DevOps architect, you should demonstrate a leadership mindset, solid operational experience, and the ability to problem-solve. Ultimately, a top-notch DevOps Architect should have exceptional communication skills, be knowledgeable about the latest industry trends, and highly innovative.

You will design a scalable back office service to manage a mobile application , and manage the product life cycle.

AWS DevOps Architect Responsibilities :
• Facilitating the development process and operations.
• Identifying setbacks and shortcomings.
• Creating suitable DevOps channels across the organization.
• Establishing continuous build environments to speed up software development.
• Designing efficient practices, architecture design using AWS Services to automate and reduce operational costs
• Delivering comprehensive best practices.
• Managing and reviewing technical operations.
• Guiding the development team.

Qualifications for AWS DevOps Architect :
• Degree in computer science, information systems, or related field.
• AWS Solution architect and / or develops Certified
• Strong Skills in Python and java
• Previous experience working on a 24x7 cloud or SaaS operation team.
• Experience with infrastructure management and monitoring.
• Strong knowledge of DevOps Platform tooling ( Chef, Puppet, and Docker.)
• Strong knowledge on API, Database, localisation services
• Working knowledge of automation service provisioning and middleware configuration.
• Ability to work independently and as part of a team (mobile developers and UI designers).
• Strong analytical skills.

AWS Services to master for this project :

App mobile
• AWS Amplify
• AWS amplify Studio
• AWS cognito
• Location Service
• API Gateway
• AWS Device Farm
• AppSync

Back end
• Cloud Watch
• Cloud trail
• Route 59
• Aurora DB
• Time stream
• Quicksight (reporting)
• SageMaker
• AWS Lambda
• AWS ECS

Ios Mobile Developer
jobs_results.description:
**Who are we?**

Founded in 2001 in Luxembourg, Vesperia has been present in France since 2014 in Paris, Île-de-France and Lille.
We specialize in technical support for web and business projects based on new development technologies.
The experience acquired during numerous missions and projects allows Vesperia to bring a real know-how to its collaborators, technical and methodological expertise (Agility, Clean Architecture, code quality...).

We offer you the opportunity to work on challenging projects and to join a friendly team:
Participate in projects in various sectors such as eCommerce, health, services, within large accounts, institutions, SMEs or **startups**.
• *The benefits**

We select for you the most interesting missions of the moment: looking for challenges and experiences that make you grow?
Vesperia places its employees at the centre of the company's project:
Social benevolence,
Financing of training and certification,
Organisation of Live Tech by our teams, sponsoring and participation in tech community events,
Provision of equipment,
Promotion of teleworking,
Valuation of your actions: cooptation, tech' event, certifications, business contribution.
• *The process**

We know that the most important thing is to meet the client's team as soon as possible: so in order not to feel like you are participating in the Hunger Games:
A discovery phone interview: your background and expectations
A meeting (HR & Manager): to discover our common paths + Tech test
Contract proposal (or not)
• *The mission**
- You will participate in the general and technical design in conjunction with the team
- You will ensure the overall technical consistency
- You are responsible for the quality of the code you produce
- You work closely with other developers, the Product Owner and other project stakeholders
- You will be responsible for testing and deployment
- You master **Swift**, Objective-C, Xcode (**at least 3 years experience**)
- You are familiar with MVVM and **RXSwift** paterns
- You have already worked with SwiftUI or are familiar with its principles
- You are comfortable with the Scrum methodology
- You are familiar with HTTP, MQTT/TLS, API Rest protocols

jobs_results.description:
**Nous offrons**:

- Mode de travail hybride (en fonction de la mission et du client)

Votre mission consistera à développer, maintenir et intégrer des systèmes propriétaires conçus en technologies mobiles iOS.

- Maîtrise du développement mobile iOS : Objective-C, Swift, SDK iOS
- Participation aux choix d'architecture logicielle en vue de la réutilisation de composants techniques
- Contribution à la réalisation des mesures d'assurance qualité du logiciel
- Connaissance de Spring est un plus pour l'implémentation des services côté serveur
- Expérience en développement Android est un atout (langage Java Android et Kotlin)
- Pratique de la méthodologie Agile (Scrum)
- Familiarité avec les frameworks de sécurité iOS
- Connaissance en encryption
- Capacité à réaliser des développements et tests unitaires
- Expérience en intégration et tests d'intégration
• *Profil**:

- Diplôme en Informatique Bac+3 min, ou équivalent
- Maîtrise parfaite du français et bonne connaissance pratique de l'anglais technique
- Sens des responsabilités et autonomie
- Orientation client
- Esprit collaboratif et capacité à travailler en équipe
- Pensée analytique et aptitude à la synthèse
- Capacité d'initiative, créativité et organisation
- Communication orale et écrite soignée et adaptée à l'interlocuteur
